students.

to ensure that attendance for the dates mentioned above is marked in the
CUMS system on the same day. This will help identify students who did not
attend their classes, and it will be assumed that such students were involved

academic rules and regulations of NSUT. The relevant clause of the
academic rules and regulations is reproduced below as ANNEXURE A. Also
procedure for claiming relaxation on medical/other grounds are placed at
ANNEXURE B.
Aid Jonge
Dean Academics
Copy for information/ necessary action:
All Dean/Directors/ HODs
CUMS with request to circulate to all course instructors/students
AR to Vice Chancellor.
AR to Registrar.
All Notice Boards
WM
 
RWN
 
PE
Page 2 of 4
ANNEXURE A
11.ATTENDANCE AND DETENTION
11.1. Students of the programme are expected to attend every lecture,
tutorial and practical class scheduled for them.
11.2. The students must have a minimum attendance of 75% of the total
number of classes including lectures, tutorials and practicals, held in a
subject till MSE/ESE in order to be eligible to appear in the MSE/ESE for
that subject.
11.3. The Dean Academics, may allow relaxation in the minimum
requirement of attendance upto 10% for reasons to be recorded. This
relaxation may be granted on the production of documents showing that the
student was either busy in any authorized activities or was absent due to
medical/other genuine reasons. The student should submit these
documents to the HoD, within seven days of resuming the studies.
Certificates submitted later will not be considered.
11.4. Under exceptional circumstances, the Dean Academics may further
relax the minimum attendance up to 5% on recommendation of a committee
comprising of Dean Student Welfare, Dean of Faculty and HoD of the
respective department.
11.5. Relaxation in attendance maybe granted for a maximum of 2 times
during the duration of the programme.
11.6. A student shall not be permitted to appear in the MSE/ESE if his/her
attendance till MSE/ESE is below 60 % after relaxation given in clauses
11.3 and 11.4.
11.7. Students who are not allowed to appear in the ESE due to shortage of
attendance shall be awarded ‘FD’ grade. Such students shall have to register
again for that course in subsequent years/Summer semester to pass the
course.
11.8. A student can register again for a different elective course in
subsequent years/Summer semester and pass the elective course.
11.9. The attendance shall be counted from the date of start of
academic session. For first semester students, attendance shall be
counted from the date of the start of academic session or the actual
date of admission, whichever is later.
Page 3 of 4
ANNEXURE B
SOME SALIENT POINTS ARE AS FOLLOWS:
a. Minimum attendance requirements are applicable to all in-house
CC/FC/FE/EO/EG/ED courses.
b. If a student is absent from the University, he/she can claim for
relaxation in minimum attendance requirements. He/she SHALL
 
NOT BE
c. Medical Certificate/Any other certificate (Authorized academic/sport
activities) of student can be accepted only within 7 days of joining the
college after medical illness is over. They should be submitted in the office of
HoD.
d. HoD shall compile the applications and forward to the office of Dean
Academic.
e. These medical certificates shall be considered (after scrutiny) for any
relaxation in attendance by the Academic Section Only.
Page 4of 4

DEPARTMENT OF ELECTRICAL ENGINEERING
B.Tech. EE 8" Semester — Presentation Schedule for Project-II (EEEEC23) End-
Semester Evaluation
Presentation Details:
e Date & Time: 19 May 2025, starting at 10:00 AM
e Venue:
o Section I: Room S-01 (Smart Block)
o Section II: Room S-02 (Smart Block)
Presentation Schedule for Section I & Il (PRESENTATIONS MUST BE PRELOADED):
e Group | to Group 12 (see next page): Report by 09:45 AM
e Group 13 to Group 23 (see next page): Report by 10:30 AM
e Groups for both the sections: https://drive.google.com/file/d/1 BqgiTXURM-
hLeSiLqVOREwEyF6-jt-8 S/view?usp=sharing
Presentation Guidelines:
e Each group will have approximately 10 minutes to present their work.
e The presence of all group members is mandatory.
e Asample PowerPoint template (in black and white format) has already been shared via Google
Classroom. Kindly ensure all text is in Times New Roman font with a WHITE
BACKGROUND.
e Attendance of all group members, including those from other sections or departments, is
mandatory.
e MOBILE PHONES ARE STRICTLY NOT ALLOWED. STUDENTS CARRYING
MOBILES SHALL BE CONSIDERED AS UNDER UFM.
Important: No changes to the presentation slots or timings will be accommodated. Students arriving
after 10:30 AM will not be allowed to present.
For any concerns, please contact:
Dr. V. S. K. V. Harish (Section I)
Dr. Ankit Kumar Singh (Section IT)
BTP Coordinators
BTP — 2 Responses received
https://drive.zoogle.com/drive/folders/1t6c4_LMHO4A-97yerv W YPF87ySEbKkH-o?usp=sharing
IN CASE OF ANY DISCREPANCY, immediately email the same with appropriate reason to:
ankit@nsut.ac.in, vskv.harish@nsut.ac.in, and to: hod.ee@nsut.ac.in.
Report Guidelines
Three copies of the report (hardbound with Royal Blue cover; see next page) must be submitted at the
time of presentation. The report must be as per the guidelines mentioned in this document. Students are
required to present a draft copy of the thesis report to the concerned supervisor at LEAST 10 DAYS
(OR AS PER THE SUPERVISOR) before the scheduled date of presentation for technical
suggestions/review.
Guidelines for Project Report
1. The project report should be meticulously typed. Photocopied reports on ready-made
material will not be entertained.
2. Plagiarism report signed by supervisors’ should be attached at the end of the report. The
similarity index should be less than 20 %.
3. 3-COPIES OF THESIS MUST BE HARD BOUND IN ROYAL BLUE COLOUR. Each
group 1s required to submit two hard-bound copies to the department; one hard-bound copy to
each supervisor.
4. The format of the cover page is given separately. This also forms the first page of the
project report.
5. Font should be Times Roman throughout the text. Font size for the text is 12pt and
Heading 14pt. Line spacing should be 1.5
6. Margins (Left = 1.5”, Right = 1”, Top= 1”, Bottom = 1”).
7. A new chapter should start with an odd page number (in case printing is done on
both sides of the sheet).
8. Equations should be written using Equation Editor (if MS Word is used). They should
be centred and numbered properly, and numbering should be kept at the extreme right.
9. Give a number to each figure in the report. Place the caption just below it.
10. Give a list of figures at the beginning of the report.
11. Place Table captions just above the table. The captions should be numbered sequentially
using Arabic numerals.
12. The references should be quoted in the text using square brackets. The references should
be kept at the end of the report. The references should be listed in the order cited in the report.
They should be written in the IEEE pattern.
Report Flow:
The report should have the following:
First page in the given format
Certificate [begin numbering pages with this page as number (1)]| [signed by Supervisors]
Acknowledgement
Plagiarism Report (less than 20%, generated from an authenticated software)
Abstract (150 words) & keywords (max 6) [in one page|
List of contents (with page numbers)
List of figures with page numbers
List of tables with page numbers
Chapter 1 (Introduction)
Chapter 2 (Decided by the guide)
Chapter 3 (Decided by the guide)
Chapter 4 (Decided by the guide)
Chapter 5 (Conclusion)
References
Appendix

Literature Survey
¢ Not more than 2 slides.
* As you have established the significance of your project area, Literature
Survey’s motives are:
1) provide an overview of the relevant and updated literature (preferably
through research papers and relevant reports).
2) to establish a context for the study using the literature.
3) identify knowledge/research gaps.
Expectations:
* Summary of the existing research on the topic, including the main
findings and conclusions (preferably through a table).
Gaps Identified
¢ Not more than 1 slide.
Expectations :
¢ A list or bullet points of the gaps or limitations in the existing research
that have been identified by you.
It's important to note that the specific contents of a slide
titled "Research Gaps Identified" will depend on the specific
research project and the findings of the research team.
Aims/Objectives of the Project
° Only one slide.
Expectations:
°A clear statement of the research problem: This should explain the
problem that the project aims to address, and why it is important.
e Research objectives: These should outline the specific goals and aims of
the research project. Each objective should be clear, concise, and
measurable.
You may also includeScope and limitations: This should explain the scope of the
research project, including what will be included and excluded from the study. It should
also outline any limitations that may affect the study's ability to achieve its objectives.
Problem Statement/Formulation/equation
° Only 1-slide
Expectations :
1) Problem formulation/Remaining Study
2) Methodology adopted
3) Technique/ approach used
4) Is Any research paper planned. If yes, then the potential journal’s/
conference’s name.
Result/Outcomes of the work
* Only 1-slide
Expectations:
1) Outcomes of the research or project, such as new knowledge gained /
new products or services developed / improvements in existing
systems or processes / social impact.
References
Format should be of IEEE Style, Font: 15/18 pts. Numbered as per the format below.
Here's an example of how to format a reference in IEEE style:
Book:
[1] A. V. Oppenheim and R. W. Schafer, Discrete-time signal processing, 3rd ed. Upper Saddle River, NJ: Prentice-Hall, 2010.
Journal article:
[2] A. Smith, “An algorithm for linearly constrained adaptive beamforming,” IEEE Trans. Antennas Propag., vol. 46, no. 2, pp. 212-221,
Feb. 1998.
Conference paper:
[3] M. K. Al-Qutayri and K. N. Salama, “High-performance mixed-signal SoC design using deep submicron technology,” in Proc. IEEE Int.
Symp. Circuits and Systems, Geneva, Switzerland, May 2000, vol. 4, pp. 321-324.
Website:
[4] IEEE Standards Association, “IEEE 802 LAN/MAN Standards Committee,” [Online]. Available:
https://standards.ieee.org/committee/802/ (accessed on Feb. 20, 2023).
Note that in IEEE style, references are numbered and listed in the order they appear in the text. The author's
name comes first, followed by the title of the article, book, or conference paper. For journal articles and
conference papers, the title of the publication is also included, along with the volume and issue number (if
applicable), the page numbers, and the date. For websites, the URL and date accessed are included.
Thank You.

Guidelines for Project Report
1. Project report should be meticulously typed. Photocopied reports on ready-made material will
not be entertained.
2. Plagiarism report signed by supervisor’s should be attached at the end of the report. The
similarity index should be less than 20 %.
3. 3-COPIES OF THESIS MUST BE HARD BOUND IN ROYAL BLUE COLOUR. Each group
is required to submit two hard bound copy to the department; one hard bound copy to each
supervisor.
4. The format of cover page is given separately. This also forms first page of the project report.
5. Font should be Times Roman throughout text. Font size for the text is 12pt and Heading 14 pt.
Line spacing should be 1.5
6. Margins (Left = 1.5”, Right = 1”, Top= 1”, Bottom = 1”).
7. A new chapter should start with odd page number (in case printing is done on both sides of
sheet).
8. Equations should be written using Equation editor (if ms word is used). They should be
centered and numbered properly, and numbering should be kept at extreme right.
9. Give anumber to each figure in the report. Place the caption just below it.
10. Give a list of figures at the beginning of the report.
11. Place Table captions just above the table. The captions should be numbered sequentially using
Arabic numerals.
12. The references should be quoted in the text using square brackets. The references should be
kept at the end of the report. The references should be listed in the order cited in the report.
They should be written in IEEE pattern.

Netaji Subhas University of Technology
(Formerly Netaji Subhas Institute of Technology)
Sector-3, Dwarka, New Delhi-110078
Department of Mechanical Engineering
Dated: 30.04.2025
Notice
End-semester presentation of M. Tech. Dissertation Phase II (MEMNCO6) shall be conducted on
20.05.2025, 9.30 am onwards at MPAE Committee room 29/VI. The Presentation shall be conducted
roll no. wise in ascending order. Students must follow the submission guidelines as stated in thesis
manual. Also report the publication based on your thesis work, if any.
Order of presentation slides shall be as follow:
1.Title slide (restricted to one page) 6.Method/Materials
